Indonesia shut down more than 1 000 local mines of coal  tin and other metals given failure to submit their 2022 work plans  Reuters cited a filing issued by the Minerals and Coal Directorate General of the mining ministry. The filing was authentic  as the officials at the mining ministry confirmed  saying the miners had been warned earlier but had yet to submit plans for 2022. Indonesia had banned exports of coal in January for a month. The shutdown of these coal mines may affect global coal supply and push up prices.
